post_text:
Welcome back RES Parents and Students!!!

We are SO EXCITED to be back in school! March 13th was a long time ago for sure, but we are confident we are ready to tackle this school year.

We have created a welcome back video to show students to ease their fears and fears/concerns of parents. My staff will also be showing this video to their classes on Wednesday, August 5th. There are many changes we have to implement to keep everyone as safe as possible during these trying times. This video will highlight some of those changes.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nH2WXY_rSdk&t=112s

post_text: Rossville Schools proudly serves students from Clinton, Carroll, Tippecanoe, and White counties. We have over 10% of our student population choosing to come to Rossville. One student's enrollment will pay for the entire mailing for newsletters to the communities we serve. Therefore, this is an excellent investment for the school corporation and is an efficient use of resources. Thank you for your comments. Our administration would be happy to discuss your concerns further. Please feel free to contact us at our corporate office at 765-379-2990.

post_text:
Dr. Tharp, Clinton County Health Officer received word from the Riley Hospital doctor caring for the 3rd grader that the child is not infectious and very low risk of spreading infection to others. There is no need for prophylactic (preventative) dose of antibiotic for students with contact to the child.

For those parents, who were able to get a dose of the Cipro antibiotic for their child/children, there is no need for worry or concern, either, as it was only one dose.

If you have any further questions, please contact your child's school administration or Nurse Janelle Pattengale at 322.
text:
Dr. Tharp, Clinton County Health Officer received word from the Riley Hospital doctor caring for the 3rd grader that the child is not infectious and very low risk of spreading infection to others. There is no need for prophylactic (preventative) dose of antibiotic for students with contact to the child.

For those parents, who were able to get a dose of the Cipro antibiotic for their child/children, there is no need for worry or concern, either, as it was only one dose.

If you have any further questions, please contact your child's school administration or Nurse Janelle Pattengale at 322.

Annual Clothing Drive--Organized by our FFA!
October 29 - November 8
We are collecting clothing for our Bountiful Harvest and need your help! We would appreciate if you could donate any new or gently used clothing! We need all types and sizes of clothing ranging from infant to adult! There will be collection tables labeled “Clothing Drive” in the hallway by the MPR where you can leave your items. We will collect the clothing at the end of every day, so keep bringing items to keep our tables full! Thank you!
